Pakistan has won the toss and elected to bowl first in the series-deciding third Twenty20 cricket international against New Zealand on Friday.The series is locked at 1-1 after Pakistan won the first match by 16 runs and New Zealand the second by 10 wickets.Pakistan made two changes to its lineup, naming Mohammad Rizwan in place of Sohaib Maqsood and Anwar Ali for Umar Gul.New Zealand made one change, bringing back strike bowler Trent Boult in place of allrounder Todd Astle.Both teams are playing their last Twenty20 before the World T20 tournament in India in March.Pakistan captain Shahid Afridi said he chose to bowl because statistics show matches at Westpac Stadium favor teams batting second.Both teams are playing their last Twenty20 before the World tournament in India in March.Lineups:New Zealand- Kane Williamson (captain), Martin Guptill, Colin Munro, Ross Taylor, Corey Anderson, Grant Elliott, Luke Ronchi, Mitchell Santner, Adam Milne, Mitchell McClenaghan, Trent Boult.Pakistan- Ahmed Shehzad, Mohammad Hafeez, Mohammad Rizwan, Shoaib Malik, Umar Akmal, Sarfraz Ahmed, Shahid Afridi (captain), Imad Wasim, Anwar Ali, Wahab Riaz, Mohammad Amir.Umpires- Billy Bowden and Derek Walker, New Zealand.TV umpire- Wayne Knights, New Zealand. Match referee- David Boon, Australia.